Brief Interpretation

  • The correlation between sanitation access and life expectancy in 2020 is 0.785, indicating a positive association.
  • Countries with higher access to basic sanitation (often >80%) tend to have life expectancy above ~70 years.
  • Countries with low sanitation access (<50%) typically exhibit substantially lower life expectancy.
  • This supports the role of water, sanitation, and hygiene (WASH) infrastructure in reducing communicable disease burden and improving population longevity.
